t cancellation, which might also help with user login hangs. I need to gather evidence from the code, especially exploring how `on_navigate` and `on_login` spawn async tasks without guards. Repeated key presses could lead to excessive tasks, spiking memory usage. I think I can minimize this by adding a gate to prevent re-entrant navigation while loading!\\n**Investigating the loading screen issue**\\n\\nI’m analyzing the issue where selecting any media item leads to a permanent loading black screen, even with a single press. This might be happening because the callback is re-entering due to home events being emitted from both the content-row and the card, potentially causing duplicate callbacks! I'll need to inspect the event chain for both the content-row and the card to see if the key press triggers both. I should check the content-row key handler to ensure it doesn’t handle both the Return and item-selected actions simultaneously, which could lead to multiple triggers. Let's dive into content-row.slint!\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_32\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"nl -ba ui/content-row.slint | sed -n '1,260p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_32\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"nl -ba ui/content-row.slint | sed -n '1,260p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"     1\\t// Jellyfin Pi TV App - Content Row Component\\n     2\\t// Horizontal scrolling row of MediaCards (Jellyfin Android TV home screen style)\\n     3\\t\\n     4\\timport { Theme, MediaItem } from \\\"theme.slint\\\";\\n     5\\timport { MediaCard } from \\\"card.slint\\\";\\n     6\\t\\n     7\\texport component ContentRow inherits VerticalLayout {\\n     8\\t    in property <string> title: \\\"\\\";\\n     9\\t    in property <[MediaItem]> items: [];\\n    10\\t    in property <bool> is-landscape: false;\\n    11\\t    in-out property <bool> row-focused: false;\\n    12\\t    in-out property <int> focused-index: 0;\\n    13\\t\\n    14\\t    callback item-selected(string);\\n    15\\t    callback item-play-requested(string);\\n    16\\t\\n    17\\t    private property <length> card-width: root.is-landscape ? Theme.landscape-width : Theme.poster-width;\\n    18\\t    private property <length> scroll-target: root.focused-index * (root.card-width + Theme.card-gap);\\n    19\\t\\n    20\\t    spacing: 0px;\\n    21\\t\\n    22\\t    // Row title\\n    23\\t    Text {\\n    24\\t        text: root.title;\\n    25\\t        font-size: Theme.font-title-medium;\\n    26\\t        font-weight: 700;\\n    27\\t        color: root.row-focused ? Theme.text-primary : Theme.text-secondary;\\n    28\\t        horizontal-alignment: left;\\n    29\\t\\n    30\\t        animate color {\\n    31\\t            duration: Theme.focus-duration;\\n    32\\t        }\\n    33\\t    }\\n    34\\t\\n    35\\t    // Spacer between title and cards\\n    36\\t    Rectangle {\\n    37\\t        height: 8px;\\n    38\\t    }\\n    39\\t\\n    40\\t    // Horizontal scrolling card strip\\n    41\\t    Flickable {\\n    42\\t        height: root.is-landscape ? Theme.landscape-height + 120px : Theme.poster-height + 120px;\\n    43\\t        viewport-width: max(self.width, root.items.length * (root.card-width + Theme.card-gap) + Theme.overscan-h * 2);\\n    44\\t\\n    45\\t        viewport-x: -root.scroll-target + Theme.overscan-h;\\n    46\\t\\n    47\\t        animate viewport-x {\\n    48\\t            duration: Theme.transition-duration;\\n    49\\t            easing: ease-in-out;\\n    50\\t        }\\n    51\\t\\n    52\\t        HorizontalLayout {\\n    53\\t            spacing: Theme.card-gap;\\n    54\\t            padding-left: Theme.overscan-h;\\n    55\\t            padding-right: Theme.overscan-h;\\n    56\\t\\n    57\\t            for item[index] in root.items : MediaCard {\\n    58\\t             