e event, especially if content-row focus is enabled. The focus scope size might complicate things further. I'm concerned that pressing “A” could trigger multiple navigation calls quickly, leading to duplicate loads and possibly endless loading issues. I should also check the login screen for similar focus scope issues causing multiple login attempts. Let’s take a closer look at login.slint for key handlers.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_34\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"FocusScope|Key.Return|select-user\\\\\\\\(|submit-password\\\\\\\\(|login\\\\\\\\(\\\\\\\" ui/login.slint | sed -n '1,200p'; nl -ba ui/login.slint | sed -n '500,700p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_34\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"FocusScope|Key.Return|select-user\\\\\\\\(|submit-password\\\\\\\\(|login\\\\\\\\(\\\\\\\" ui/login.slint | sed -n '1,200p'; nl -ba ui/login.slint | sed -n '500,700p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"148:    callback select-user(string);\\n149:    callback submit-password(string, string);\\n529:    key-handler := FocusScope {\\n548:                if (event.text == Key.Return) {\\n558:                            root.select-user(root.users[root.focused-user].id);\\n603:                if (event.text == Key.Return) {\\n625:                            root.submit-password(root.selected-user-id, root.password-input);\\n   500\\t                    vertical-alignment: center;\\n   501\\t                }\\n   502\\t            }\\n   503\\t        }\\n   504\\t\\n   505\\t        Text {\\n   506\\t            text: \\\"Authorize this code in your Jellyfin app\\\";\\n   507\\t            font-size: Theme.font-body-medium;\\n   508\\t            color: Theme.text-secondary;\\n   509\\t            horizontal-alignment: center;\\n   510\\t        }\\n   511\\t\\n 