{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"reasoning","text":"**Evaluating issue handling**\n\nI’m thinking about whether the system might panic when indexing rows that are empty, especially when the Enter key is pressed. It could lead to out-of-bounds errors if I’m not careful. The problem seems to happen with any media selection. \n\nI’ll check the media card's selected callback to see what’s going on there. Strong logging around navigation and loading could help, but I know I need a minimal fix. Implementing \"single-flight detail navigation\" seems like the right approach. This will help prevent unnecessary duplicate requests.\n**Implementing cancel functionality**\n\nTo handle escape cancellation, I can introduce a cancellation token whenever the user goes back or navigates away. This way, the loading task checks the token before making any UI updates and related loads. If the token changes, I'll abort early to prevent any screen overwriting. This should directly address the concern that \"Escape should cancel loading and go back.\" \n\nI'll also need to add `use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicU64, Ordering};` and check the imports to see if it’s already in use."}}
