{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_56","type":"agent_message","text":"Done — I fixed one P0 issue end-to-end and pushed it.\n\n**What I Fixed (P0)**\n- Added a navigation in-flight guard for `\"detail\"` loads to prevent repeated `A/Enter` presses from spawning overlapping detail requests that keep the loading overlay stuck and drive memory up (`src/main.rs:618`, `src/main.rs:670`).\n- The guard is released on success/error and on CollectionFolder redirect path, so detail navigation can recover cleanly (`src/main.rs:714`, `src/main.rs:743`).\n- `go-back()` now always clears loading state and resets that guard, so Escape/B reliably cancels out of stuck loading flows (`src/main.rs:820`).\n\n**Validation**\n- `cargo check` passes locally (warnings only, no errors).\n- Commit: `8423d4b` on `slint-rewrite`.\n- Pushed to `origin/slint-rewrite`.\n- Latest CI: GitHub Actions run `24333157853` is `in_progress` (`Secret Guard` workflow).\n\n**What to Test on Pi**\n- From Home, press `A` on an item repeatedly: should open detail once, not black-screen lock.\n- From Login, select a user: should transition to Home without permanent `Loading...`.\n- While loading overlay is visible, press `B/Escape`: should always back out and clear loading."}}
